channel.title: Trying to list my own server. IP found on machine does not match
channel.description:
Okay so check it out, im hosting a server on IP address 205.237.129.6. I tried to list that server on moparcraft right? It tells me to use a browser on my server machine and go to a link right? So i got to that link on the server machine and it gives me this: Error: 205.237.129.6 resolves to 205.237.129.6, which does not match your ip, 205.237.137.114.
No. the IP of my server has not changed. I can connect to my minecraft server just fine on the IP 205.237.129.6 and I'm connected to the server machine where the minecraft server is running plane as day on 205.237.129.6. Now.... why does it think that my IP is 205.237.137.114?

item.title: Trying to list my own server. IP found on machine does not match
item.dc:creator: @CoonHunter CoonHunter
item.description:
@CoonHunter wrote:

Do the entire process on the server machine, It might be using the IP which you made the request on, and not considering that you the server is being run on a completely different network.
